--Roman Number Converter
Roman number converter is a Python code for converting roman numerals to arabic and vice versa. The converter is multiligual and supports 24 languages.

--Installation
Dowload folder number_converter_beta

You need to have working Python development environment to run the python code. The input and output will be through the environment's console.
If you do not have any suitable environment, you can download Spyder here: https://www.spyder-ide.org/
Instal Spyder fy following the instructions in the instalation wizard.
If you do not have Python installed into your device, you can download and instal it here: https://www.python.org/downloads/.
To install follow the instructions in the instalation wizard.

--Usage
Open folder number_converter_beta and run file run_app.py in the Spyder environment. Press 'Run file' button. Choose the language and press enter. 
Enter the numbers that you want to convert into the console, and press enter.

